** How socket is implemented in Hermes ?
** What is the difference between Topic and Queue in EMS ?
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Topic                                                                              | Queue                                                                                         |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Topic is shared datastructure. Server pulish it into Topic.                        | Each client has individual queue. Server create individual messages and sends to the clients. |
| Clients fetches the copy  from the topic.                                          | Client dequeue it.                                                                            |
| Message in Topic is removed once all the clients got the copy.                     | Queue is persistant.                                                                          |
| Topic is transient.                                                                | Queue is point-to-point.                                                                      |
| If message is sent on topic,who ever subscribed at that time only get a copy each. | In queue case, each subscriber will not get a copy of same message but distinct messages.     |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|

** Two process sharing a file . Make sure they are synchronized and no one get starved if there is continues flow of data (both for read and write).
